              orcid: "ORCID : 0000-0001-5414-2803",
              aboutData: `Dr. Umesh Kumar Singh is currently working as an Assistant Professor in the Mechanical Engineering Department at Shri Ramswaroop Memorial College of Engineering and Management, Lucknow. He is a dedicated academic and researcher specializing in Friction Stir Welding (FSW), Advanced Manufacturing, Numerical Simulation, and Optimization Techniques. Dr. Singh earned his Ph.D. from MNNIT Allahabad in 2023, where his research focused on developing an indigenous FSW setup and evaluating the welding performance of dissimilar magnesium alloys. He has published multiple high-impact research papers in SCI, SCIE, and Scopus-indexed journals and has presented his work at prestigious international conferences, including ASME MSEC (USA), UNAM-IEC (University of Namibia), and events organized by IITs and NITs. His research contributions have garnered over 98 citations, with an h-index of 6 and an i10-index of 4. Alongside his research, Dr. Singh is passionate about teaching and possesses 2 years of academic experience. He has also co-authored two textbooks. `,
